metadata.name: dab #7
metadata.description:
To create an expressive design with bold colors and intricate details, I used small, quick strokes and changed directions to create texture and depth.
Whether abstract, contemporary, or traditional, They inspired me, and I often tried to create vibrant and visually striking compositions to create a sense of movement and energy in my work and to make it an appealing and captivating form of artistic expression.

Made by p5.js
s = save

metadata.name: Zena #120
metadata.description:
Zena is a study of creating complex patterns via manipulating particle angles using math, bitwise operators and noise.

It can take up to a minute to render or longer in low-performance computers. Enjoy the process!

----Best experienced in full screen----

Probabilities;

- 7 different patterns

- 4 frame types

- 2 frame colors

- 4 different particle hues (Rare; full spectrum) 

- Rare; circular placement

- Rare; dark background

You can right click and save as .png (or press 's' in liveMode) once the rendering is done.



Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, September 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Voltage Vipers Automaton #109
metadata.description:
Multiple snakes feed with electricity, grow, and are definitely going to lose the game and transform into an electrical circuit cellular automaton.

Press 's' to save a gif.
Press 'p' to stop/start the pulse.
Press 'a' to stop/start the animation.
Click on a wire cell to generate an electron.

metadata.name: Cosmic Poems #342
metadata.description:
Cosmic Poems is the fourth iteration of my work that explores the algorithmic space of typography. In this new piece, I expand on my initial inspirations of the early concrete poetry movement bringing in texts of my own. These short texts are taken from my extensive notes on the subject of artificial intelligence. Snippets of plausible pistes of reflection as well as lighter more tongue in cheek ideas make up the selection I have curated for the work. I hope that it may engage your attention with pleasure. 

Keys : ’s’ to save PNG

Program written by Mark Webster
Font design by simonrenaud.fr

mwebster.online
@motiondesign_01
